Interface CaseClass

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FlexiblyEqual
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCaseClass, SimpleCaseClass

    public interface CaseClass
    An aggregate of multiple components (values with names) allowing various utilities to be applied concisely.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void buildResult(ResultBuilder builder)
      Adds the components to the given ResultBuilder.

    • Method Detail

      • buildResult

        void buildResult(ResultBuilder builder)
        Adds the components to the given ResultBuilder. To implement, repeatedly call builder.add with values that the object is composed of and a name of your choice. Avoid redundant values that can be computed from others. Since the builder returns itself, multiple calls can be chained. For example: builder.add("name", name).add("age", age).add(...);

        Note that adding a value to a builder exposes it as part of the class's interface, so if you don't want to have a public getter method for a value, you probably don't want to add it here.
